Review Text: I ordered a shredded chicken omlet where I found only 5 small pieces of chicken in the omlet and the price is like 125 without tax. Food I ordered doesn't satisfy hunger and I recommend not to order any item from this restaurant. Food is not worthy at all.

Ordered omu fried rice. It was literally an omelette and a few spoons of fried rice. The quantity is so less it wouldn't even fill a child and it's for 114 plus tax plus delivery. You can see in the picture the amount is not even half the box it came in. Plus ordered lemon tea. Not a hint of lemon and was so sweet, couldn't even have more than 1 sip. Very disappointed.

The fried rice and noodles I ordered was very bad. It's is not worth the money at all. I ordered fresh lime juice and it tasted just like plain sugar water. I will not recommend this restaurant to anyone nor order from this restaurant again.

Taste is good but prices are exorbitant. We will feel that all Omelettes are similar in one way or the other but prices vary vastly. They take a lot of time to prepare even we have the food at the Restaurant. So the popularity has gone down drastically now.

Tea parcel is not upto the mark, Tea is parcelled in a plastic bag that is not at all hygienic and hotness is not there after delivery. Delivery charge is 10 rupees in what basis. I will suggest some healthy container that will keep the hotness for atleast an hour that is delivery time.

This is what almost sub standard food in inadequate quantity looks like. I ordered the egg-chicken Maggi and egg salad. I doubt if there was any chicken in the Maggi. Both the items were done fine, but it was nothing different or value adding. The taste was average and quantity below average. So, at the price this becomes costlier and poor on value for money.
Healthy food at night. Enjoyed the taste. Recommended for late night hunger. Even early delivery of food is appreciable. Thanks for the white egg omelette loved it.
